<br>
It depends..<br>
<br>
The ISS, at full (apparently, not likely to be achieved) buildout, would have used 100 KWe.<br>
<br>
The McMurdo Antarctic station uses about 1500 KWe.<br>
<br>
Thus, a typical ~6 member Mars ship would likely use something in the mid hundreds of Kilowatts<br>
<br>
The drive reactor could easily supply that power.<br>
<br>
For redundency sake tho, multiple reactors make sense - particularly if you carry one down to the surface. A reactor brought down by a lander would be fresh and unused. The dangers and operational complications of landing with, then installing, a &quot;hot&quot; reactor would be contraindicated.<br>
<br>
Even with the major weight penalty, three reactors may be an optimal number for a VASIMR.<br>
